&lt;P&gt;Both will not do very good DPS - that quite frankly is because we aren't allowed to be the masters of all weapons - Knights are special and get near Epic Quality 1Handers, while we have to make do with weapons intended to be weilded two at a time. We can pay AA (when we're high enough in level) to get some small improvement and get the equivilant of a small ratio boost - while Knights get huge ratio boost absolutely FREE.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;It sounds good in theory, but take out a Paladin with a BoFF with aggro proc and a 2.0 with 2 aggro procs (since you can) and the swing aggro gap is fairly sizeable. Also you must remember that all Knight triple attack AAs are aimed at 2h use only. Whereas Warriors can quadruple attack without restriction. Knights do trade out a fair amount of aggro to use a 1h actually. Also we trade out a lot of DPS for using a 1h weapon.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Also talking about things one class gets and another doesn't. Paladins don't get the possibility of wielding 4 procs. We don't get a natural aggro modifier for being who we are. We get one aggro mod item which kinda sucks really.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Yet again I still agree with Warriors being able to use shields from 100% to 0%, but don't be under the illusion that there's no trade off, that's just naive.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;</description>
