&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Ability #4707: Veteran's Fury &lt;BR&gt;Description: Increases damage dealt when you land a critical hit on a melee attack by 10% per rank. This ability does not affect special attacks. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 3&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Ability #4722: Mercy Kill &lt;BR&gt;Description: Increases the level of NPCs that can be slain by your finishing blow to 66, 68 and 70 per rank. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 3 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Ability #4725: Rage of Serpent Spine &lt;BR&gt;Description: Each rank of this ability increases the maximum amount of attack you can gain from items. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 5 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Ability #4730: Endurance of Serpent Spine &lt;BR&gt;Description: This ability increases your natural endurance regeneration by 1 point per rank. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 5 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Ability #4733: Greater Ingenuity &lt;BR&gt;Description: Years of experimentation have led to the discovery of how to gain additional performance (in the form of critical spell hits) from weapons and other items. Each rank in this ability should increase your critical hit chance with such items by 3% per rank. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 1 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Ability #4736: Ingenuity Mastery &lt;BR&gt;Description: Extensive experimentation has enabled you to deal more damage with your critical hits done by spells and abilities of magical and mechanical items. Each rank in this ability increases the crit damage of such items by 10% per rank. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 1 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Ability #4739: Killing Spree &lt;BR&gt;Description: After slaying an enemy, you have a 3% chance per rank to enter a battle frenzy that increases your offensive damage for the next thirty seconds. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 5 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Ability #4742: Hold the Line &lt;BR&gt;Description: Hold the Line increases the amount of hit points healed by healing spells that land on you by 10%, but reduces your offensive damage by 25% as well. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 5 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;All those are in except Ingenuity Mastery it appears, which got the axe...&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Ability #591: Savage Onslaught &lt;BR&gt;Description: This ability increases the chance to make a flurry attack upon a successful triple attack. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 5 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;Yes, there's another 3 levels of Flurry&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Ability #618: Overbear &lt;BR&gt;Description: This ability gives you a chance to bypass your opponents' special defenses such as dodge, block, parry, and riposte. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 3 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;I don't remember if this got the axe or not, I don't beleieve it did.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Ability #605: Shield Specialist &lt;BR&gt;Description: As long as a shield is equipped, each rank in Shield Specialist confers a 2% damage bonus to attacks made by a weapon held in a warrior's primary hand. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 5 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;BR&gt;This has been dramatically changed.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;Each rank gives 5% more damage in the primary hand when a shield is equipped in the offhand.&amp;nbsp; There are 5 levels, so this confers a 25% boost to main hand damage when maxed while a shield is equipped in the offhand.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;Also, as a secondary feature to go along with this, but usable at all times, Mock and it's upgrade, Scowl, have been moved to their own timer separate from Bazu AND Cyclone Blade (And it's upgrade, Vortex Blade).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; This is a pretty dramatic upgrade, you'll want to watch your END, cause you'll be able to burn through it SUPER fast.&amp;nbsp; The good news is the ooc combat regen rate is VERY high, I was able to go from 0 to 13k endurance in 2 mins once I hit the regen timer.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Ability #606: Mark of the Mage Hunter &lt;BR&gt;Description: When activated, Mark of the Mage Hunter reduces the damage of incoming spells by 200. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 9 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;BR&gt;This is a really sweet AA, and it's had it's timer removed, there's a max absorbed of 5khp.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Ability #607: Hamstring &lt;BR&gt;Description: Hamstring is a crippling attack that slows your opponents' movement rate and reduces their ability to effectively use armor for a short peroid of time. Each additional rank in Hamstring increases the amount of AC denied by the Hamstring attack. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 3 &lt;BR&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Hamstring got the axe... in it's place, we're getting 5 more levels of Sturdiness.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;EM&gt;&lt;SPAN class=postbody&gt;Ability #611: Battle Leap &lt;BR&gt;Description: Battle Leap enables you to spring forward into combat. Your momentum will confer a boost to your attacks for a short period of time. When used, Battle Leap will remove any levitation effects. &lt;BR&gt;Cost per Level: 9 &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I love this AA, for the fun more than anything else.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; It shoots you about 100 feet in the direction you're facing and gives you a pretty decent attack boost.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The primary use in my view is&amp;nbsp;for engaging raid NPC's giving you a big jump ahead of others to let you gank initial aggro fast.&amp;nbsp;It's also helpful for running away from mobs.&amp;nbsp; &#xD;
&lt;P&gt;One that was also missed was Grapple, which is a reverse of Press the Attack, with a shorter refresh.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
